<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="27" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,438,718]" pageId="6" pageNumber="27">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,266,438,463]" pageId="6" pageNumber="27">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. Frons with large punctures (rugose appearance), occipital carina present, notauli crenulate, striate sculpturing on second metasomal tergum, fore wing hyaline with 2 
<superScript attach="left" box="[930,946,473,487]" fontSize="6" pageId="6" pageNumber="27">nd</superScript>
submarginal cell short (3RSa less than or equal to 2RS), m-cu arising directly in line with 2RS, hind wing RS absent and m-cu present.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="27" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,438,718]" pageId="6" pageNumber="27">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,328,548,573]" pageId="6" pageNumber="27">Comments</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Sonan" baseAuthorityYear="1932" box="[349,538,550,573]" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Fopius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="arisanus">
<emphasis box="[349,538,550,573]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="27">Fopius arisanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is easily separated from the other species discussed here, by its strongly sculptured body and dark thoracic pleura and abdomen. It is native to the Indo-Pacific Region and is an egg-larval parasitoid of fruit flies. It was introduced from Florida to 
<collectingCountry box="[800,868,621,646]" name="Brazil" pageId="6" pageNumber="27">Brazil</collectingCountry>
by “Embrapa Semiárido” in 2012 (
<bibRefCitation author="Paranhos, B. A. J. &amp; Sa, L. A. N. &amp; Manoukis, N. C. &amp; Prado, S. S. &amp; Morelli, R. &amp; Nava, D. E. &amp; Lima, A. L. &amp; Jang, E. E." pageId="6" pageNumber="27" pagination="1" refId="ref8261" refString="Paranhos, B. A. J., Sa, L. A. N., Manoukis, N. C., Prado, S. S., Morelli, R., Nava, D. E., Lima, A. L. &amp; Jang, E. E. (2013) Competicao interespecifica entre o parasitoide exotico Fopius arisanus e o nativo Doryctobracon areolatus (Hymenoptera: Braconidae) em Anastrepha fraterculus (Diptera: Tephritidae). XIII Simposio de Controle Biologico, Bonito, MT, 2013, 1." type="journal article" year="2013">
Paranhos 
<emphasis box="[1380,1436,621,646]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="27">et al.</emphasis>
2013
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Santos, J. O. &amp; Carvalho, G. K. L. &amp; Pacheco, M. G. &amp; Costa, M. L. E. &amp; Macedo, A. T. &amp; Sa, L. A. N. &amp; Gama, F. C. &amp; Paranhos, B. J." box="[223,433,657,682]" pageId="6" pageNumber="27" pagination="1" refId="ref8613" refString="Santos, J. O., Carvalho, G. K. L., Pacheco, M. G., Costa, M. L. E., Macedo, A. T., Sa, L. A. N., Gama, F. C. &amp; Paranhos, B. J. (2014) Introducao do parasitoide de ovos Fopius arisanus (Sonan, 1932) (Hymenoptera: Braconidae) no Brasil e sua multiplicacao sobre mosca do mediterraneo. XXV Congresso Brasileiro de Entomologia, Goiania, Goias, 2014, 1." type="journal article" year="2014">
Santos 
<emphasis box="[307,358,657,682]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="27">et al</emphasis>
. 2014
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Sa, L. A. N. &amp; Pessoa, M. C. P. Y." box="[446,660,657,682]" pageId="6" pageNumber="27" pagination="256 - 274" refId="ref8505" refString="Sa, L. A. N. &amp; Pessoa, M. C. P. Y. (2015) Prospeccao de inimigos naturais para o controle biologico de pragas agricolas exoticas. In: Sugayama, R. L., Silva, M. L. da, Silva, S. X. de B., Ribeiro, L. C. &amp; Rangel, L. E. P. (Eds.), Defesa vegetal: fundamentos, ferramentas, politicas e perspectivas. Sociedade Brasileira de Defesa Agropecuaria, Belo Horizonte, pp. 256 - 274." type="book chapter" year="2015">Sá &amp; Pessoa 2015</bibRefCitation>
). In 
<collectingCountry box="[712,783,657,682]" name="Brazil" pageId="6" pageNumber="27">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, it is being studied to control 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Wiedemann" baseAuthorityYear="1830" box="[1128,1386,657,682]" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Anastrepha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fraterculus">
<emphasis box="[1128,1386,657,682]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="27">Anastrepha fraterculus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Groth et al. 2016)" authorityName="Groth" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Groth" baseAuthorityYear="2016" box="[151,575,693,718]" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Ceratitis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="capitata">
<emphasis box="[151,348,694,717]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="27">Ceratitis capitata</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Groth, M. Z. &amp; Loeck, A. E. &amp; Nornberg, S. D. &amp; Bernardi, D. &amp; Nava, D. E." box="[369,567,693,718]" pageId="6" pageNumber="27" pagination="96" refId="ref7238" refString="Groth, M. Z., Loeck, A. E., Nornberg, S. D., Bernardi, D. &amp; Nava, D. E. (2016) Biology of Fopius arisanus (Hymenoptera: Braconidae) in two species of fruit flies. Journal of Insect Science, 16, 96. https: // doi. org / 10.1093 / jisesa / iew 087" type="journal article" year="2016">
Groth 
<emphasis box="[443,492,693,718]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="27">et al</emphasis>
. 2016
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
